@Sal\_vager for the logs is it after I exit the game?

Also I might have figured out the cause, the cause is the sm3 shaders being turned on. But I remembered that I had that setting turned on before 1.0 and no problems. So wierd. Also it looks terrible with it off

**Edited <time datetime="2015-05-10T22:34:46Z" title="05/10/2015 10:34  PM" data-short="9 yr">May 10, 2015</time> by tempsgk**

@komodo just tried that setting, holy .... it works! Normal FPS. Tested an assortment of settings. sm3 shaders with fast rendering = Works! Sm3 Shaders with Simple and above rendering = Fps cut in half when looking at horizon, Turning Off Sm3 shaders with any rendering setting = Works.

@Sal\_Vager

